# Iron & Ale Copilot Instructions

You are assisting in building the Iron & Ale site.  
Apply the same neon design system consistently across all HTML, CSS, and JS files.

## Guidance Level: Novice Mode
- Assume developer is a beginner.
- Provide step-by-step scaffolds for HTML, CSS, and JS.
- Add explanatory comments in code to clarify purpose of each section.
- Suggest safe defaults before advanced options.
- Keep examples simple, modular, and easy to test in browser.
- Use semantic HTML5 and accessible ARIA attributes consistently.
- Highlight where code can be extended later, but don’t overwhelm with complexity.

## Global HTML Layout
- Use semantic HTML5 tags: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <footer>.
- Include hero banner with neon flicker heading and silhouettes on index.html.
- Sticky navigation bar with logo, links, hamburger menu, overlay, and close button.
- Footer with social links and consistent neon styling.
- Ensure aria-current for active nav link and ARIA attributes for accessibility.

## Page Section Structures
- index.html → Hero banner, intro sections, CTA buttons.
- events.html → Upcoming events grid with neon cards, CTA buttons, modal details.
- past-events.html → Archived events list with neon badges, modal details.
- timers.html → Countdown timer section with neon glow digits and progress rings.
- wods.html → Workout of the Day entries with neon section headers.
- wods-table.html → Tabular workout data with neon borders and hover highlights.
- benchmarks.html → Benchmark workout sections with neon emphasis on titles/categories.
- pr-tracker.html → Personal record tracker with neon progress bars and glowing indicators.
- wod-generator.html → Generator form with neon inputs, glowing submit button.
- leaderboard.html → Leaderboard table with neon highlights for top ranks.
- admin-events.html → Admin event management with neon-styled forms and buttons.
- 24hr-workout.html → Special challenge page with neon countdown, progress tracker, event details.

## Constraints
- Keep layouts responsive across desktop and mobile.
- Preserve accessibility with labels and ARIA attributes.
- Maintain consistent neon theme across all sections.

